HEADWORD: Inelastic
<hw>In`e*las"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Not
elastic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Economics)</fld> <def>reacting little to changing
price; -- of demand; <as>as, Potatoes have an <ex>inelastic</ex>
demand</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inelasticity</ent>⟦br⟧
